{
  "stem": "19111.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they were.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were so many different roundups every-- practically every week or every other day at that time, in the beginning, especially.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They rounded up-- they wanted to diminish the Jewish population, and there were some of my cousins that were caught.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't know at the time that they were being killed, you know?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We thought that they were taken to somewheres to work.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But after-- after these few months, the Germans have announced that actually what happened was they cleared a certain section in the center if Vilna was a-- where mostly Jewish people lived.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They took all the inhabitants out of this section, and they disappeared.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They took them away.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They took him to the Lukiskes prison from where we found out later that they were all taken to Ponary and shot dead over there.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so this area that they cleared of inhabitants, they also had some Polish people had to move out of there, and they formed the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Actually, they formed two ghettos next to each other where they-- one street, the [INAUDIBLE] Street, which is actually translated German street, in between as a border dividing the ghetto number one and ghetto number two.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then the order came that all the Jews from the entire city of Vilna must move to the ghetto, to the designated area, and they can only take with them only the things that they can carry with them.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You're not allowed to have any-- any horse and wagon or any kind of other transportation.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Only what you can carry on your back.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I believe that it had to be, let's see, April, June-- I would imagine about September.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "To be exact, September 6, 1941.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
